29 inline Operand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return Operand(ebp, -offset); }

31 inline MemOperand GetHalfStackSlot(int offset, RegPairHalf half) {
32  int32_t half_offset =
33  half == kLowWord ? 0 : LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize / 2;
34  return Operand(offset > 0 ? ebp : esp, -offset + half_offset);
35 }

42 inline Operand MemOperand(Register base, Register offset_reg, int offset_imm) {
43  return offset_reg == no_reg ? Operand(base, offset_imm)
44  : Operand(base, offset_reg, times_1, offset_imm);
45 }

47 static constexpr LiftoffRegList kByteRegs =
48  LiftoffRegList::FromBits<RegList{eax, ecx, edx}.bits()>();
49 
50 inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, Register base,
51  int32_t offset, ValueKind kind) {
52  Operand src(base, offset);
53  switch (kind) {
54  case kI16:
55  assm->mov_w(dst.gp(), src);
56  break;
57  case kI32:
58  case kRefNull:
59  case kRef:
60  assm->mov(dst.gp(), src);
61  break;
62  case kI64:
63  assm->mov(dst.low_gp(), src);
64  assm->mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(base, offset + 4));
65  break;
66  case kF32:
67  assm->movss(dst.fp(), src);
68  break;
69  case kF64:
70  assm->movsd(dst.fp(), src);
71  break;
72  case kS128:
73  assm->movdqu(dst.fp(), src);
74  break;
75  case kVoid:
76  case kTop:
77  case kBottom:
78  case kI8:
79  case kF16:
80  UNREACHABLE();
81  }
82 }
83 
84 inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register base, int32_t offset,
85  LiftoffRegister src, ValueKind kind) {
86  Operand dst(base, offset);
87  switch (kind) {
88  case kI16:
89  assm->mov_w(dst, src.gp());
90  break;
91  case kI32:
92  case kRefNull:
93  case kRef:
94  assm->mov(dst, src.gp());
95  break;
96  case kI64:
97  assm->mov(dst, src.low_gp());
98  assm->mov(Operand(base, offset + 4), src.high_gp());
99  break;
100  case kF32:
101  assm->movss(dst, src.fp());
102  break;
103  case kF64:
104  assm->movsd(dst, src.fp());
105  break;
106  case kS128:
107  assm->movdqu(dst, src.fp());
108  break;
109  case kVoid:
110  case kTop:
111  case kBottom:
112  case kI8:
113  case kF16:
114  UNREACHABLE();
115  }
116 }
117 
118 inline void push(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind,
119  int padding = 0) {
120  switch (kind) {
121  case kI32:
122  case kRef:
123  case kRefNull:
124  assm->AllocateStackSpace(padding);
125  assm->push(reg.gp());
126  break;
127  case kI64:
128  assm->AllocateStackSpace(padding);
129  assm->push(reg.high_gp());
130  assm->push(reg.low_gp());
131  break;
132  case kF32:
133  assm->AllocateStackSpace(sizeof(float) + padding);
134  assm->movss(Operand(esp, 0), reg.fp());
135  break;
136  case kF64:
137  assm->AllocateStackSpace(sizeof(double) + padding);
138  assm->movsd(Operand(esp, 0), reg.fp());
139  break;
140  case kS128:
141  assm->AllocateStackSpace(sizeof(double) * 2 + padding);
142  assm->movdqu(Operand(esp, 0), reg.fp());
143  break;
144  case kVoid:
145  case kTop:
146  case kBottom:
147  case kI8:
148  case kI16:
149  case kF16:
150  UNREACHABLE();
151  }
152 }

154 inline void SignExtendI32ToI64(Assembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg) {
155  assm->mov(reg.high_gp(), reg.low_gp());
156  assm->sar(reg.high_gp(), 31);
157 }

159 // Get a temporary byte register, using {candidate} if possible.
160 // Might spill, but always keeps status flags intact.
161 inline Register GetTmpByteRegister(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register candidate) {
162  if (candidate.is_byte_register()) return candidate;
163  // {GetUnusedRegister()} may insert move instructions to spill registers to
164  // the stack. This is OK because {mov} does not change the status flags.
165  return assm->GetUnusedRegister(liftoff::kByteRegs).gp();
166 }
167 
168 inline void MoveStackValue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, const Operand& src,
169  const Operand& dst) {
170  if (assm->cache_state()->has_unused_register(kGpReg)) {
171  Register tmp = assm->cache_state()->unused_register(kGpReg).gp();
172  assm->mov(tmp, src);
173  assm->mov(dst, tmp);
174  } else {
175  // No free register, move via the stack.
176  assm->push(src);
177  assm->pop(dst);
178  }
179 }
180 
181 class CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters {
182  public:
183  explicit CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
184  LiftoffRegList pinned = {})
185  : assm_(assm), pinned_(pinned) {}
186 
187  ~CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters() {
188  for (Register reg : must_pop_) {
189  assm_->pop(reg);
190  }
191  }
192 
193  Register Acquire() {
194  if (assm_->cache_state()->has_unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_)) {
195  return pinned_.set(
196  assm_->cache_state()->unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_).gp());
197  }
198 
199  RegList available =
200  kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs - pinned_.GetGpList() - must_pop_;
201  DCHECK(!available.is_empty());
202  // Use {last()} here so we can just iterate forwards in the destructor.
203  Register reg = available.last();
204  assm_->push(reg);
205  must_pop_.set(reg);
206  return reg;
207  }
208 
209  private:
210  LiftoffAssembler* const assm_;
211  LiftoffRegList pinned_;
212  RegList must_pop_;
213 };

224 int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
225  int offset = pc_offset();
226  // Next we reserve the memory for the whole stack frame. We do not know yet
227  // how big the stack frame will be so we just emit a placeholder instruction.
228  // PatchPrepareStackFrame will patch this in order to increase the stack
229  // appropriately.
230  sub_sp_32(0);
231  DCHECK_EQ(liftoff::kSubSpSize, pc_offset() - offset);
232  return offset;
233 }

235 void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
236 // The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
237 // `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
238 #ifdef __clang__
239  static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
240  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
241  kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
242  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
243 #endif
244 
245  LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
246  WasmValue(declared_function_index));
247  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
248 }
249 
250 void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
251  int stack_param_delta) {
252  // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
253  push(Operand(ebp, 4));
254  push(Operand(ebp, 0));
255 
256  // Shift the whole frame upwards.
257  Register scratch = eax;
258  push(scratch);
259  const int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
260  for (int i = slot_count; i > 0; --i) {
261  mov(scratch, Operand(esp, i * 4));
262  mov(Operand(ebp, (i - stack_param_delta - 1) * 4), scratch);
263  }
264  pop(scratch);
265 
266  // Set the new stack and frame pointers.
267  lea(esp, Operand(ebp, -stack_param_delta * 4));
268  pop(ebp);
269 }

271 void LiftoffAssembler::AlignFrameSize() {}

273 void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
274  int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
275  bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
276  // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
277  // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
278  // for them anymore.
279  int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
280  // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
281  if (feedback_vector_slot) {
282  frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
283  }
284  DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_size % kSystemPointerSize);
285 
286  // We can't run out of space when patching, just pass anything big enough to
287  // not cause the assembler to try to grow the buffer.
288  constexpr int kAvailableSpace = 64;
289  Assembler patching_assembler(
290  AssemblerOptions{},
291  ExternalAssemblerBuffer(buffer_start_ + offset, kAvailableSpace));
292 
293  if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
294  // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
295  // done with it.
296  patching_assembler.sub_sp_32(frame_size);
297  DCHECK_EQ(liftoff::kSubSpSize, patching_assembler.pc_offset());
298  return;
299  }
300 
301  // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
302  // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
303  // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
304  // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
305  // replace the {__ sub(sp, framesize)} with a jump to OOL code that does this
306  // "extended stack check".
307  //
308  // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
309  // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
310  // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
311  // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
312  // large frame.
313 
314  // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
315  // {pc_offset()}).
316  patching_assembler.jmp_rel(pc_offset() - offset);
317  DCHECK_GE(liftoff::kSubSpSize, patching_assembler.pc_offset());
318  patching_assembler.Nop(liftoff::kSubSpSize - patching_assembler.pc_offset());
319 
320  // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
321  // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
322  // check in the condition code.
323  RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
324  Label continuation;
325  if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
326  // We do not have a scratch register, so pick any and push it first.
327  Register stack_limit = eax;
328  push(stack_limit);
329  mov(stack_limit, esp);
330  sub(stack_limit, Immediate(frame_size));
331  CompareStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
332  pop(stack_limit);
333  j(above_equal, &continuation, Label::kNear);
334  }
335 
336  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
337  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
338  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
339  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
340  for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
341  for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
342  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
343  mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(),
344  Immediate(frame_size));
345  mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), ebp);
346  add(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(),
347  Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(
348  stack_param_slots * kSystemPointerSize +
349  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp)));
350  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
351  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
352  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
353  } else {
354  wasm_call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
355  RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
356  // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
357  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
358  AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromWasmTrap);
359  }
360 
361  bind(&continuation);
362 
363  // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
364  // decrementing the SP; consult {MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace}.
365  AllocateStackSpace(frame_size);
366 
367  // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
368  // right after the reserved space for the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} (which
369  // is a branch now).
370  int func_start_offset = offset + liftoff::kSubSpSize;
371  jmp_rel(func_start_offset - pc_offset());
372 }

391 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
392  Label* ool_label,
393  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
394  {
395  liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this};
396  Register budget_array = temps.Acquire();
397 
398  Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
399  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
400  instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the temp register.
401  LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
402  }
403 
404  constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
405  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
406  mov(budget_array, Operand{instance_data, kArrayOffset});
407 
408  int array_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
409  sub(Operand{budget_array, array_offset}, Immediate(budget_used));
410  }
411  j(negative, ool_label);
412 }
413 
414 Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
415  if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
416  return ebp;
417  }
418  Label done, call_runtime;
419  cmp(MemOperand(ebp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset),
420  Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
421  j(equal, &call_runtime);
422  LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
423  mov(old_fp.gp(), ebp);
424  jmp(&done);
425 
426  bind(&call_runtime);
427  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
428  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
429  PrepareCallCFunction(1, eax);
430  MacroAssembler::Move(Operand(esp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize),
431  Immediate(ExternalReference::isolate_address()));
432  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
433  if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
434  mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
435  }
436  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
437 
438  bind(&done);
439  return old_fp.gp();
440 }
441 
442 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
443  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
444  for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
445  for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
446  cmp(MemOperand(ebp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset),
447  Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
448  Label done;
449  j(not_equal, &done);
450  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
451  PrepareCallCFunction(1, kReturnRegister0);
452  MacroAssembler::Move(Operand(esp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize),
453  Immediate(ExternalReference::isolate_address()));
454  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
455  // Restore old ebp. We don't need to restore old esp explicitly, because
456  // it will be restored from ebp in LeaveFrame before return.
457  mov(ebp, kReturnRegister0);
458  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
459  bind(&done);
460 }
461 
462 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
463  switch (value.type().kind()) {
464  case kI32:
465  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.gp(), Immediate(value.to_i32()));
466  break;
467  case kI64: {
468  int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
469  int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
470  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.low_gp(), Immediate(low_word));
471  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.high_gp(), Immediate(high_word));
472  break;
473  }
474  case kF32:
475  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f32_boxed().get_bits());
476  break;
477  case kF64:
478  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits());
479  break;
480  default:
481  UNREACHABLE();
482  }
483 }

496 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
497  int offset, int size) {
498  DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
499  Operand src{instance, offset};
500  switch (size) {
501  case 1:
502  movzx_b(dst, src);
503  break;
504  case 4:
505  mov(dst, src);
506  break;
507  default:
508  UNIMPLEMENTED();
509  }
510 }

557 
558 void LiftoffAssembler::EmitWriteBarrier(Register target_object,
559  Operand store_location,
560  Register stored_value,
561  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
562  liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this, pinned};
563  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
564 
565  Label exit;
566  CheckPageFlag(target_object, scratch,
567  MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &exit,
568  Label::kNear);
569  JumpIfSmi(stored_value, &exit, Label::kNear);
570  CheckPageFlag(stored_value, scratch,
571  MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &exit,
572  Label::kNear);
573  lea(scratch, store_location);
574  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(target_object, scratch,
575  SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
576  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
577  bind(&exit);
578 }
579 
580 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
581  Register offset_reg,
582  int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
583  LiftoffRegList pinned,
584  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
585  SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
586  DCHECK_GE(offset_imm, 0);
587  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
588  static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt32Size);
589  Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
590 
591  if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
592 
593  mov(dst_op, src);
594 
595  if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
596  EmitWriteBarrier(dst_addr, dst_op, src, pinned);
597 }
598 
599 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStoreTaggedPointer(
600  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
601  LiftoffRegList pinned, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order,
602  uint32_t* protected_store_pc) {
603  StoreTaggedPointer(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, src, pinned,
604  protected_store_pc);
605 }
606 
607 void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
608  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
609  LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
610  bool /* is_load_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */,
611  bool needs_shift) {
612  // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
613  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
614  DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, dst.is_gp_pair());
615  ScaleFactor scale_factor =
616  !needs_shift ? times_1 : static_cast<ScaleFactor>(type.size_log_2());
617  Operand src_op = offset_reg == no_reg ? Operand(src_addr, offset_imm)
618  : Operand(src_addr, offset_reg,
619  scale_factor, offset_imm);
620  if (protected_load_pc) *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
621 
622  switch (type.value()) {
623  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
624  movzx_b(dst.gp(), src_op);
625  break;
626  case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
627  movsx_b(dst.gp(), src_op);
628  break;
629  case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
630  movzx_b(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
631  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
632  break;
633  case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
634  movsx_b(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
635  liftoff::SignExtendI32ToI64(this, dst);
636  break;
637  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
638  movzx_w(dst.gp(), src_op);
639  break;
640  case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
641  movsx_w(dst.gp(), src_op);
642  break;
643  case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
644  movzx_w(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
645  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
646  break;
647  case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
648  movsx_w(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
649  liftoff::SignExtendI32ToI64(this, dst);
650  break;
651  case LoadType::kI32Load:
652  mov(dst.gp(), src_op);
653  break;
654  case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
655  mov(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
656  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
657  break;
658  case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
659  mov(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
660  liftoff::SignExtendI32ToI64(this, dst);
661  break;
662  case LoadType::kI64Load: {
663  // Compute the operand for the load of the upper half.
664  Operand upper_src_op =
665  liftoff::MemOperand(src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm + 4);
666  // The high word has to be mov'ed first, such that this is the protected
667  // instruction. The mov of the low word cannot segfault.
668  mov(dst.high_gp(), upper_src_op);
669  mov(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
670  break;
671  }
672  case LoadType::kF32Load:
673  movss(dst.fp(), src_op);
674  break;
675  case LoadType::kF64Load:
676  movsd(dst.fp(), src_op);
677  break;
678  case LoadType::kS128Load:
679  movdqu(dst.fp(), src_op);
680  break;
681  case LoadType::kF32LoadF16:
682  UNIMPLEMENTED();
683  break;
684  }
685 }
686 
687 void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
688  uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
689  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
690  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
691  bool /* is_store_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */) {
692  DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, src.is_gp_pair());
693  // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
694  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
695  Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
696  if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
697 
698  switch (type.value()) {
699  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
700  src = src.low();
701  [[fallthrough]];
702  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
703  // Only the lower 4 registers can be addressed as 8-bit registers.
704  if (src.gp().is_byte_register()) {
705  mov_b(dst_op, src.gp());
706  } else {
707  // We know that {src} is not a byte register, so the only pinned byte
708  // registers (beside the outer {pinned}) are {dst_addr} and potentially
709  // {offset_reg}.
710  LiftoffRegList pinned_byte = pinned | LiftoffRegList{dst_addr};
711  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned_byte.set(offset_reg);
712  LiftoffRegList candidates = liftoff::kByteRegs.MaskOut(pinned_byte);
713  if (cache_state_.has_unused_register(candidates)) {
714  Register byte_src = cache_state_.unused_register(candidates).gp();
715  mov(byte_src, src.gp());
716  mov_b(dst_op, byte_src);
717  } else {
718  // We have no available byte register. We will temporarily push the
719  // root register to use it as a scratch register.
720  static_assert(kRootRegister == ebx);
721  Register byte_src = kRootRegister;
722  Push(byte_src);
723  mov(byte_src, src.gp());
724  mov_b(dst_op, byte_src);
725  Pop(byte_src);
726  }
727  }
728  break;
729  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
730  src = src.low();
731  [[fallthrough]];
732  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
733  mov_w(dst_op, src.gp());
734  break;
735  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
736  src = src.low();
737  [[fallthrough]];
738  case StoreType::kI32Store:
739  mov(dst_op, src.gp());
740  break;
741  case StoreType::kI64Store: {
742  // Compute the operand for the store of the upper half.
743  Operand upper_dst_op =
744  liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm + 4);
745  // The high word has to be mov'ed first, such that this is the protected
746  // instruction. The mov of the low word cannot segfault.
747  mov(upper_dst_op, src.high_gp());
748  mov(dst_op, src.low_gp());
749  break;
750  }
751  case StoreType::kF32Store:
752  movss(dst_op, src.fp());
753  break;
754  case StoreType::kF64Store:
755  movsd(dst_op, src.fp());
756  break;
757  case StoreType::kS128Store:
758  Movdqu(dst_op, src.fp());
759  break;
760  case StoreType::kF32StoreF16:
761  UNIMPLEMENTED();
762  break;
763  }
764 }
765 
766 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
767  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
768  LoadType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
769  bool /* i64_offset */) {
770  if (type.value() != LoadType::kI64Load) {
771  Load(dst, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, type, nullptr, true);
772  return;
773  }
774 
775  DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, dst.is_gp_pair());
776  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
777  Operand src_op = liftoff::MemOperand(src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
778 
779  movsd(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, src_op);
780  Pextrd(dst.low().gp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, 0);
781  Pextrd(dst.high().gp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, 1);
782 }
783 
784 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
785  uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
786  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
787  bool /* i64_offset */) {
788  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
789  Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
790 
791  // i64 store uses a totally different approach, hence implement it separately.
792  if (type.value() == StoreType::kI64Store) {
793  auto scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned).fp();
794  movd(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, src.low().gp());
795  movd(scratch2, src.high().gp());
796  Punpckldq(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, scratch2);
797  movsd(dst_op, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
798  // This lock+or is needed to achieve sequential consistency.
799  lock();
800  or_(Operand(esp, 0), Immediate(0));
801  return;
802  }
803 
804  // Other i64 stores actually only use the low word.
805  if (src.is_pair()) src = src.low();
806  Register src_gp = src.gp();
807 
808  bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
809  LiftoffRegList src_candidates =
810  is_byte_store ? liftoff::kByteRegs : kGpCacheRegList;
811  pinned = pinned | LiftoffRegList{dst_addr, src};
812  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
813 
814  // Ensure that {src} is a valid and otherwise unused register.
815  if (!src_candidates.has(src) || cache_state_.is_used(src)) {
816  // If there are no unused candidate registers, but {src} is a candidate,
817  // then spill other uses of {src}. Otherwise spill any candidate register
818  // and use that.
819  LiftoffRegList unpinned_candidates = src_candidates.MaskOut(pinned);
820  if (!cache_state_.has_unused_register(unpinned_candidates) &&
821  src_candidates.has(src)) {
822  SpillRegister(src);
823  } else {
824  Register safe_src = GetUnusedRegister(unpinned_candidates).gp();
825  mov(safe_src, src_gp);
826  src_gp = safe_src;
827  }
828  }
829 
830  switch (type.value()) {
831  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
832  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
833  xchg_b(src_gp, dst_op);
834  return;
835  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
836  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
837  xchg_w(src_gp, dst_op);
838  return;
839  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
840  case StoreType::kI32Store:
841  xchg(src_gp, dst_op);
842  return;
843  default:
844  UNREACHABLE();
845  }
846 }
847 
848 namespace liftoff {
849 #define __ lasm->
850 
851 enum Binop { kAdd, kSub, kAnd, kOr, kXor, kExchange };
852 
853 inline void AtomicAddOrSubOrExchange32(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Binop binop,
854  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
855  uint32_t offset_imm,
856  LiftoffRegister value,
857  LiftoffRegister result, StoreType type) {
858  DCHECK_EQ(value, result);
859  DCHECK(!__ cache_state()->is_used(result));
860  bool is_64_bit_op = type.value_type() == kWasmI64;
861 
862  Register value_reg = is_64_bit_op ? value.low_gp() : value.gp();
863  Register result_reg = is_64_bit_op ? result.low_gp() : result.gp();
864 
865  bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
866  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg};
867  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
868 
869  // Ensure that {value_reg} is a valid register.
870  if (is_byte_store && !liftoff::kByteRegs.has(value_reg)) {
871  Register safe_value_reg =
872  __ GetUnusedRegister(liftoff::kByteRegs.MaskOut(pinned)).gp();
873  __ mov(safe_value_reg, value_reg);
874  value_reg = safe_value_reg;
875  }
876 
877  Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
878  if (binop == kSub) {
879  __ neg(value_reg);
880  }
881  if (binop != kExchange) {
882  __ lock();
883  }
884  switch (type.value()) {
885  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
886  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
887  if (binop == kExchange) {
888  __ xchg_b(value_reg, dst_op);
889  } else {
890  __ xadd_b(dst_op, value_reg);
891  }
892  __ movzx_b(result_reg, value_reg);
893  break;
894  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
895  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
896  if (binop == kExchange) {
897  __ xchg_w(value_reg, dst_op);
898  } else {
899  __ xadd_w(dst_op, value_reg);
900  }
901  __ movzx_w(result_reg, value_reg);
902  break;
903  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
904  case StoreType::kI32Store:
905  if (binop == kExchange) {
906  __ xchg(value_reg, dst_op);
907  } else {
908  __ xadd(dst_op, value_reg);
909  }
910  if (value_reg != result_reg) {
911  __ mov(result_reg, value_reg);
912  }
913  break;
914  default:
915  UNREACHABLE();
916  }
917  if (is_64_bit_op) {
918  __ xor_(result.high_gp(), result.high_gp());
919  }
920 }
921 
922 inline void AtomicBinop32(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Binop op, Register dst_addr,
923  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
924  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
925  StoreType type) {
926  DCHECK_EQ(value, result);
927  DCHECK(!__ cache_state()->is_used(result));
928  bool is_64_bit_op = type.value_type() == kWasmI64;
929 
930  Register value_reg = is_64_bit_op ? value.low_gp() : value.gp();
931  Register result_reg = is_64_bit_op ? result.low_gp() : result.gp();
932 
933  // The cmpxchg instruction uses eax to store the old value of the
934  // compare-exchange primitive. Therefore we have to spill the register and
935  // move any use to another register.
936  {
937  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg};
938  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
939  __ ClearRegister(eax, {&dst_addr, &offset_reg, &value_reg}, pinned);
940  }
941 
942  bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
943  Register scratch = no_reg;
944  if (is_byte_store) {
945  // The scratch register has to be a byte register. As we are already tight
946  // on registers, we just use the root register here.
947  static_assert(!kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs.has(kRootRegister),
948  "root register is not Liftoff cache register");
949  DCHECK(kRootRegister.is_byte_register());
950  __ push(kRootRegister);
951  scratch = kRootRegister;
952  } else {
953  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg, eax};
954  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
955  scratch = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
956  }
957 
958  Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
959 
960  switch (type.value()) {
961  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
962  case StoreType::kI64Store8: {
963  __ xor_(eax, eax);
964  __ mov_b(eax, dst_op);
965  break;
966  }
967  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
968  case StoreType::kI64Store16: {
969  __ xor_(eax, eax);
970  __ mov_w(eax, dst_op);
971  break;
972  }
973  case StoreType::kI32Store:
974  case StoreType::kI64Store32: {
975  __ mov(eax, dst_op);
976  break;
977  }
978  default:
979  UNREACHABLE();
980  }
981 
982  Label binop;
983  __ bind(&binop);
984  __ mov(scratch, eax);
985 
986  switch (op) {
987  case kAnd: {
988  __ and_(scratch, value_reg);
989  break;
990  }
991  case kOr: {
992  __ or_(scratch, value_reg);
993  break;
994  }
995  case kXor: {
996  __ xor_(scratch, value_reg);
997  break;
998  }
999  default:
1000  UNREACHABLE();
1001  }
1002 
1003  __ lock();
1004 
1005  switch (type.value()) {
1006  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1007  case StoreType::kI64Store8: {
1008  __ cmpxchg_b(dst_op, scratch);
1009  break;
1010  }
1011  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1012  case StoreType::kI64Store16: {
1013  __ cmpxchg_w(dst_op, scratch);
1014  break;
1015  }
1016  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1017  case StoreType::kI64Store32: {
1018  __ cmpxchg(dst_op, scratch);
1019  break;
1020  }
1021  default:
1022  UNREACHABLE();
1023  }
1024  __ j(not_equal, &binop);
1025 
1026  if (is_byte_store) {
1027  __ pop(kRootRegister);
1028  }
1029  if (result_reg != eax) {
1030  __ mov(result_reg, eax);
1031  }
1032  if (is_64_bit_op) {
1033  __ xor_(result.high_gp(), result.high_gp());
1034  }
1035 }
1036 
1037 inline void AtomicBinop64(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Binop op, Register dst_addr,
1038  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1039  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result) {
1040  // We need {ebx} here, which is the root register. As the root register it
1041  // needs special treatment. As we use {ebx} directly in the code below, we
1042  // have to make sure here that the root register is actually {ebx}.
1043  static_assert(kRootRegister == ebx,
1044  "The following code assumes that kRootRegister == ebx");
1045  __ push(ebx);
1046 
1047  // Store the value on the stack, so that we can use it for retries.
1048  __ AllocateStackSpace(8);
1049  Operand value_op_hi = Operand(esp, 0);
1050  Operand value_op_lo = Operand(esp, 4);
1051  __ mov(value_op_lo, value.low_gp());
1052  __ mov(value_op_hi, value.high_gp());
1053 
1054  // We want to use the compare-exchange instruction here. It uses registers
1055  // as follows: old-value = EDX:EAX; new-value = ECX:EBX.
1056  Register old_hi = edx;
1057  Register old_lo = eax;
1058  Register new_hi = ecx;
1059  Register new_lo = ebx;
1060  // Base and offset need separate registers that do not alias with the
1061  // ones above.
1062  Register base = esi;
1063  Register offset = edi;
1064 
1065  // Spill all these registers if they are still holding other values.
1066  __ SpillRegisters(old_hi, old_lo, new_hi, base, offset);
1067  if (offset_reg == no_reg) {
1068  if (dst_addr != base) __ mov(base, dst_addr);
1069  offset = no_reg;
1070  } else {
1071  // Potentially swap base and offset register to avoid unnecessary moves.
1072  if (dst_addr == offset || offset_reg == base) {
1073  std::swap(dst_addr, offset_reg);
1074  }
1075  __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1076  {{LiftoffRegister{base}, LiftoffRegister{dst_addr}, kI32},
1077  {LiftoffRegister{offset}, LiftoffRegister{offset_reg}, kI32}});
1078  }
1079 
1080  Operand dst_op_lo = liftoff::MemOperand(base, offset, offset_imm);
1081  Operand dst_op_hi = liftoff::MemOperand(base, offset, offset_imm + 4);
1082 
1083  // Load the old value from memory.
1084  __ mov(old_lo, dst_op_lo);
1085  __ mov(old_hi, dst_op_hi);
1086  Label retry;
1087  __ bind(&retry);
1088  __ mov(new_lo, old_lo);
1089  __ mov(new_hi, old_hi);
1090  switch (op) {
1091  case kAdd:
1092  __ add(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1093  __ adc(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1094  break;
1095  case kSub:
1096  __ sub(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1097  __ sbb(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1098  break;
1099  case kAnd:
1100  __ and_(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1101  __ and_(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1102  break;
1103  case kOr:
1104  __ or_(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1105  __ or_(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1106  break;
1107  case kXor:
1108  __ xor_(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1109  __ xor_(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1110  break;
1111  case kExchange:
1112  __ mov(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1113  __ mov(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1114  break;
1115  }
1116  __ lock();
1117  __ cmpxchg8b(dst_op_lo);
1118  __ j(not_equal, &retry);
1119 
1120  // Deallocate the stack space again.
1121  __ add(esp, Immediate(8));
1122  // Restore the root register, and we are done.
1123  __ pop(kRootRegister);
1124 
1125  // Move the result into the correct registers.
1126  __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1127  {{result, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(old_lo, old_hi), kI64}});
1128 }
1129 
1130 #undef __
1131 } // namespace liftoff

1217 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(
1218  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1219  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
1220  DCHECK_NE(value, result);
1221  Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1222  mov(result.gp(), value.gp());
1223  xchg(result.gp(), dst_op);
1224  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
1225  EmitWriteBarrier(dst_addr, dst_op, value.gp(), pinned);

1227 
1228 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
1229  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1230  LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
1231  StoreType type, bool /* i64_offset */) {
1232  // We expect that the offset has already been added to {dst_addr}, and no
1233  // {offset_reg} is provided. This is to save registers.
1234  DCHECK_EQ(offset_reg, no_reg);
1235 
1236  DCHECK_EQ(result, expected);
1237 
1238  if (type.value() != StoreType::kI64Store) {
1239  bool is_64_bit_op = type.value_type() == kWasmI64;
1240 
1241  Register value_reg = is_64_bit_op ? new_value.low_gp() : new_value.gp();
1242  Register expected_reg = is_64_bit_op ? expected.low_gp() : expected.gp();
1243  Register result_reg = expected_reg;
1244 
1245  // The cmpxchg instruction uses eax to store the old value of the
1246  // compare-exchange primitive. Therefore we have to spill the register and
1247  // move any use to another register.
1248  ClearRegister(eax, {&dst_addr, &value_reg},
1249  LiftoffRegList{dst_addr, value_reg, expected_reg});
1250  if (expected_reg != eax) {
1251  mov(eax, expected_reg);
1252  expected_reg = eax;
1253  }
1254 
1255  bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
1256  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg, expected_reg};
1257 
1258  // Ensure that {value_reg} is a valid register.
1259  if (is_byte_store && !liftoff::kByteRegs.has(value_reg)) {
1260  Register safe_value_reg =
1261  pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(liftoff::kByteRegs.MaskOut(pinned)))
1262  .gp();
1263  mov(safe_value_reg, value_reg);
1264  value_reg = safe_value_reg;
1265  pinned.clear(LiftoffRegister(value_reg));
1266  }
1267 
1268  Operand dst_op = Operand(dst_addr, offset_imm);
1269 
1270  lock();
1271  switch (type.value()) {
1272  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1273  case StoreType::kI64Store8: {
1274  cmpxchg_b(dst_op, value_reg);
1275  movzx_b(result_reg, eax);
1276  break;
1277  }
1278  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1279  case StoreType::kI64Store16: {
1280  cmpxchg_w(dst_op, value_reg);
1281  movzx_w(result_reg, eax);
1282  break;
1283  }
1284  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1285  case StoreType::kI64Store32: {
1286  cmpxchg(dst_op, value_reg);
1287  if (result_reg != eax) {
1288  mov(result_reg, eax);
1289  }
1290  break;
1291  }
1292  default:
1293  UNREACHABLE();
1294  }
1295  if (is_64_bit_op) {
1296  xor_(result.high_gp(), result.high_gp());
1297  }
1298  return;
1299  }
1300 
1301  // The following code handles kExprI64AtomicCompareExchange.
1302 
1303  // We need {ebx} here, which is the root register. The root register it
1304  // needs special treatment. As we use {ebx} directly in the code below, we
1305  // have to make sure here that the root register is actually {ebx}.
1306  static_assert(kRootRegister == ebx,
1307  "The following code assumes that kRootRegister == ebx");
1308  push(kRootRegister);
1309 
1310  // The compare-exchange instruction uses registers as follows:
1311  // old-value = EDX:EAX; new-value = ECX:EBX.
1312  Register expected_hi = edx;
1313  Register expected_lo = eax;
1314  Register new_hi = ecx;
1315  Register new_lo = ebx;
1316  // The address needs a separate registers that does not alias with the
1317  // ones above.
1318  Register address = esi;
1319 
1320  // Spill all these registers if they are still holding other values.
1321  SpillRegisters(expected_hi, expected_lo, new_hi, address);
1322 
1323  // We have to set new_lo specially, because it's the root register. We do it
1324  // before setting all other registers so that the original value does not get
1325  // overwritten.
1326  mov(new_lo, new_value.low_gp());
1327 
1328  // Move all other values into the right register.
1329  ParallelRegisterMove(
1330  {{LiftoffRegister(address), LiftoffRegister(dst_addr), kI32},
1331  {LiftoffRegister::ForPair(expected_lo, expected_hi), expected, kI64},
1332  {LiftoffRegister(new_hi), new_value.high(), kI32}});
1333 
1334  Operand dst_op = Operand(address, offset_imm);
1335 
1336  lock();
1337  cmpxchg8b(dst_op);
1338 
1339  // Restore the root register, and we are done.
1340  pop(kRootRegister);
1341 
1342  // Move the result into the correct registers.
1343  ParallelRegisterMove(
1344  {{result, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(expected_lo, expected_hi), kI64}});
1345 }

1369 void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1370  ValueKind kind) {
1371  DCHECK_EQ(0, SlotSizeForType(kind) % kSystemPointerSize);
1372  int words = SlotSizeForType(kind) / kSystemPointerSize;
1373  DCHECK_LE(1, words);
1374  // Make sure we move the words in the correct order in case there is an
1375  // overlap between src and dst.
1376  if (src_offset < dst_offset) {
1377  do {
1378  liftoff::MoveStackValue(this, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset),
1379  liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1380  dst_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1381  src_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1382  } while (--words);
1383  } else {
1384  while (words--) {
1385  liftoff::MoveStackValue(
1386  this, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset - words * kSystemPointerSize),
1387  liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset - words * kSystemPointerSize));
1388  }
1389  }
1390 }

1394  DCHECK(kI32 == kind || is_reference(kind));

1396 }

1398 void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1399  ValueKind kind) {
1400  DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1401  if (kind == kF32) {
1402  movss(dst, src);
1403  } else if (kind == kF64) {
1404  movsd(dst, src);
1405  } else {
1406  DCHECK_EQ(kS128, kind);
1407  Movaps(dst, src);
1408  }
1409 }

1411 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1412  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1413  Operand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1414  switch (kind) {
1415  case kI32:
1416  case kRefNull:
1417  case kRef:
1418  mov(dst, reg.gp());
1419  break;
1420  case kI64:
1421  mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kLowWord), reg.low_gp());
1422  mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kHighWord), reg.high_gp());
1423  break;
1424  case kF32:
1425  movss(dst, reg.fp());
1426  break;
1427  case kF64:
1428  movsd(dst, reg.fp());
1429  break;
1430  case kS128:
1431  movdqu(dst, reg.fp());
1432  break;
1433  default:
1434  UNREACHABLE();
1435  }
1436 }
1437 
1438 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1439  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1440  Operand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1441  switch (value.type().kind()) {
1442  case kI32:
1443  mov(dst, Immediate(value.to_i32()));
1444  break;
1445  case kI64: {
1446  int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
1447  int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
1448  mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kLowWord), Immediate(low_word));
1449  mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kHighWord), Immediate(high_word));
1450  break;
1451  }
1452  default:
1453  // We do not track f32 and f64 constants, hence they are unreachable.
1454  UNREACHABLE();
1455  }
1456 }

1460 }

1466 void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1467  DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1468  DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 4);
1469  RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1470 
1471  if (size <= 12) {
1472  // Special straight-line code for up to three words (6-9 bytes per word:
1473  // C7 <1-4 bytes operand> <4 bytes imm>, makes 18-27 bytes total).
1474  for (int offset = 4; offset <= size; offset += 4) {
1475  mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(start + offset, kLowWord), Immediate(0));
1476  }
1477  } else {
1478  // General case for bigger counts.
1479  // This sequence takes 19-22 bytes (3 for pushes, 3-6 for lea, 2 for xor, 5
1480  // for mov, 3 for repstosq, 3 for pops).
1481  // Note: rep_stos fills ECX doublewords at [EDI] with EAX.
1482  push(eax);
1483  push(ecx);
1484  push(edi);
1485  lea(edi, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + size));
1486  xor_(eax, eax);
1487  // Size is in bytes, convert to doublewords (4-bytes).
1488  mov(ecx, Immediate(size / 4));
1489  rep_stos();
1490  pop(edi);
1491  pop(ecx);
1492  pop(eax);
1493  }
1494 }
1495 
1496 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadSpillAddress(Register dst, int offset,
1497  ValueKind /* kind */) {
1498  lea(dst, liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset));
1499 }

1517 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sub(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs) {
1518  if (dst != rhs) {
1519  // Default path.
1520  if (dst != lhs) mov(dst, lhs);
1521  sub(dst, rhs);
1522  } else if (lhs == rhs) {
1523  // Degenerate case.
1524  xor_(dst, dst);
1525  } else {
1526  // Emit {dst = lhs + -rhs} if dst == rhs.
1527  neg(dst);
1528  add(dst, lhs);
1529  }
1530 }

1534  // We'll have to implement an UB-safe version if we need this corner case.
1535  DCHECK_NE(imm, kMinInt);
1536  lea(dst, Operand(lhs, -imm));
1537  } else {
1538  sub(dst, Immediate(imm));
1539  }
1540 }

1542 namespace liftoff {
1543 template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register)>
1544 void EmitCommutativeBinOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst, Register lhs,
1545  Register rhs) {
1546  if (dst == rhs) {
1547  (assm->*op)(dst, lhs);
1548  } else {
1549  if (dst != lhs) assm->mov(dst, lhs);
1550  (assm->*op)(dst, rhs);
1551  }
1552 }
1553 
1554 template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, int32_t)>
1555 void EmitCommutativeBinOpImm(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst, Register lhs,
1556  int32_t imm) {
1557  if (dst != lhs) assm->mov(dst, lhs);
1558  (assm->*op)(dst, imm);
1559 }
1560 } // namespace liftoff

1574 namespace liftoff {
1575 enum class DivOrRem : uint8_t { kDiv, kRem };
1576 template <bool is_signed, DivOrRem div_or_rem>
1577 void EmitInt32DivOrRem(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst, Register lhs,
1578  Register rhs, Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1579  Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1580  constexpr bool needs_unrepresentable_check =
1581  is_signed && div_or_rem == DivOrRem::kDiv;
1582  constexpr bool special_case_minus_1 =
1583  is_signed && div_or_rem == DivOrRem::kRem;
1584  DCHECK_EQ(needs_unrepresentable_check, trap_div_unrepresentable != nullptr);
1585 
1586  // For division, the lhs is always taken from {edx:eax}. Thus, make sure that
1587  // these registers are unused. If {rhs} is stored in one of them, move it to
1588  // another temporary register.
1589  // Do all this before any branch, such that the code is executed
1590  // unconditionally, as the cache state will also be modified unconditionally.
1591  assm->SpillRegisters(eax, edx);
1592  if (rhs == eax || rhs == edx) {
1593  LiftoffRegList unavailable{eax, edx, lhs};
1594  Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, unavailable).gp();
1595  assm->mov(tmp, rhs);
1596  rhs = tmp;
1597  }
1598 
1599  // Check for division by zero.
1600  assm->test(rhs, rhs);
1601  assm->j(zero, trap_div_by_zero);
1602 
1603  Label done;
1604  if (needs_unrepresentable_check) {
1605  // Check for {kMinInt / -1}. This is unrepresentable.
1606  Label do_div;
1607  assm->cmp(rhs, -1);
1608  assm->j(not_equal, &do_div);
1609  assm->cmp(lhs, kMinInt);
1610  assm->j(equal, trap_div_unrepresentable);
1611  assm->bind(&do_div);
1612  } else if (special_case_minus_1) {
1613  // {lhs % -1} is always 0 (needs to be special cased because {kMinInt / -1}
1614  // cannot be computed).
1615  Label do_rem;
1616  assm->cmp(rhs, -1);
1617  assm->j(not_equal, &do_rem);
1618  assm->xor_(dst, dst);
1619  assm->jmp(&done);
1620  assm->bind(&do_rem);
1621  }
1622 
1623  // Now move {lhs} into {eax}, then zero-extend or sign-extend into {edx}, then
1624  // do the division.
1625  if (lhs != eax) assm->mov(eax, lhs);
1626  if (is_signed) {
1627  assm->cdq();
1628  assm->idiv(rhs);
1629  } else {
1630  assm->xor_(edx, edx);
1631  assm->div(rhs);
1632  }
1633 
1634  // Move back the result (in {eax} or {edx}) into the {dst} register.
1635  constexpr Register kResultReg = div_or_rem == DivOrRem::kDiv ? eax : edx;
1636  if (dst != kResultReg) assm->mov(dst, kResultReg);
1637  if (special_case_minus_1) assm->bind(&done);
1638 }
1639 } // namespace liftoff

1690 namespace liftoff {
1691 inline void EmitShiftOperation(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
1692  Register src, Register amount,
1693  void (Assembler::*emit_shift)(Register)) {
1694  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src, amount};
1695  // If dst is ecx, compute into a tmp register first, then move to ecx.
1696  if (dst == ecx) {
1697  Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1698  assm->mov(tmp, src);
1699  if (amount != ecx) assm->mov(ecx, amount);
1700  (assm->*emit_shift)(tmp);
1701  assm->mov(ecx, tmp);
1702  return;
1703  }
1704 
1705  // Move amount into ecx. If ecx is in use, move its content to a tmp register
1706  // first. If src is ecx, src is now the tmp register.
1707  Register tmp_reg = no_reg;
1708  if (amount != ecx) {
1709  if (assm->cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(ecx)) ||
1710  pinned.has(LiftoffRegister(ecx))) {
1711  tmp_reg = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1712  assm->mov(tmp_reg, ecx);
1713  if (src == ecx) src = tmp_reg;
1714  }
1715  assm->mov(ecx, amount);
1716  }
1717 
1718  // Do the actual shift.
1719  if (dst != src) assm->mov(dst, src);
1720  (assm->*emit_shift)(dst);
1721 
1722  // Restore ecx if needed.
1723  if (tmp_reg.is_valid()) assm->mov(ecx, tmp_reg);
1724 }
1725 } // namespace liftoff
1726 
1727 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shl(Register dst, Register src,
1728  Register amount) {
1729  liftoff::EmitShiftOperation(this, dst, src, amount, &Assembler::shl_cl);

1775 namespace liftoff {
1776 template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register),
1777  void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, Register)>
1778 inline void OpWithCarry(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
1779  LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
1780  // First, compute the low half of the result, potentially into a temporary dst
1781  // register if {dst.low_gp()} equals {rhs.low_gp()} or any register we need to
1782  // keep alive for computing the upper half.
1783  LiftoffRegList keep_alive{lhs.high_gp(), rhs};
1784  Register dst_low = keep_alive.has(dst.low_gp())
1785  ? assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, keep_alive).gp()
1786  : dst.low_gp();
1787 
1788  if (dst_low != lhs.low_gp()) assm->mov(dst_low, lhs.low_gp());
1789  (assm->*op)(dst_low, rhs.low_gp());
1790 
1791  // Now compute the upper half, while keeping alive the previous result.
1792  keep_alive = LiftoffRegList{dst_low, rhs.high_gp()};
1793  Register dst_high = keep_alive.has(dst.high_gp())
1794  ? assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, keep_alive).gp()
1795  : dst.high_gp();
1796 
1797  if (dst_high != lhs.high_gp()) assm->mov(dst_high, lhs.high_gp());
1798  (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst_high, rhs.high_gp());
1799 
1800  // If necessary, move result into the right registers.
1801  LiftoffRegister tmp_result = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high);
1802  if (tmp_result != dst) assm->Move(dst, tmp_result, kI64);
1803 }
1804 
1805 template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, const Immediate&),
1806  void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, int32_t)>
1807 inline void OpWithCarryI(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
1808  LiftoffRegister lhs, int64_t imm) {
1809  // The compiler allocated registers such that either {dst == lhs} or there is
1810  // no overlap between the two.
1811  DCHECK_NE(dst.low_gp(), lhs.high_gp());
1812 
1813  int32_t imm_low_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm);
1814  int32_t imm_high_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm >> 32);
1815 
1816  // First, compute the low half of the result.
1817  if (dst.low_gp() != lhs.low_gp()) assm->mov(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp());
1818  (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), Immediate(imm_low_word));
1819 
1820  // Now compute the upper half.
1821  if (dst.high_gp() != lhs.high_gp()) assm->mov(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp());
1822  (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst.high_gp(), imm_high_word);
1823 }
1824 } // namespace liftoff

1841 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1842  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
1843  // Idea:
1844  // [ lhs_hi | lhs_lo ] * [ rhs_hi | rhs_lo ]
1845  // = [ lhs_hi * rhs_lo | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
1846  // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_hi | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
1847  // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_lo ] (32x32->64 mul, shift 0)
1848 
1849  // For simplicity, we move lhs and rhs into fixed registers.
1850  Register dst_hi = edx;
1851  Register dst_lo = eax;
1852  Register lhs_hi = ecx;
1853  Register lhs_lo = dst_lo;
1854  Register rhs_hi = dst_hi;
1855  Register rhs_lo = esi;
1856 
1857  // Spill all these registers if they are still holding other values.
1858  SpillRegisters(dst_hi, dst_lo, lhs_hi, rhs_lo);
1859 
1860  // Move lhs and rhs into the respective registers.
1861  ParallelRegisterMove({{LiftoffRegister::ForPair(lhs_lo, lhs_hi), lhs, kI64},
1862  {LiftoffRegister::ForPair(rhs_lo, rhs_hi), rhs, kI64}});
1863 
1864  // First mul: lhs_hi' = lhs_hi * rhs_lo.
1865  imul(lhs_hi, rhs_lo);
1866  // Second mul: rhi_hi' = rhs_hi * lhs_lo.
1867  imul(rhs_hi, lhs_lo);
1868  // Add them: lhs_hi'' = lhs_hi' + rhs_hi' = lhs_hi * rhs_lo + rhs_hi * lhs_lo.
1869  add(lhs_hi, rhs_hi);
1870  // Third mul: edx:eax (dst_hi:dst_lo) = eax * esi (lhs_lo * rhs_lo).
1871  mul(rhs_lo);
1872  // Add lhs_hi'' to dst_hi.
1873  add(dst_hi, lhs_hi);
1874 
1875  // Finally, move back the temporary result to the actual dst register pair.
1876  LiftoffRegister dst_tmp = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_lo, dst_hi);
1877  if (dst != dst_tmp) Move(dst, dst_tmp, kI64);
1878 }

1905 namespace liftoff {
1906 inline bool PairContains(LiftoffRegister pair, Register reg) {
1907  return pair.low_gp() == reg || pair.high_gp() == reg;
1908 }
1909 
1910 inline LiftoffRegister ReplaceInPair(LiftoffRegister pair, Register old_reg,
1911  Register new_reg) {
1912  if (pair.low_gp() == old_reg) {
1913  return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(new_reg, pair.high_gp());
1914  }
1915  if (pair.high_gp() == old_reg) {
1916  return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(pair.low_gp(), new_reg);
1917  }
1918  return pair;
1919 }
1920 
1921 inline void Emit64BitShiftOperation(
1922  LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
1923  Register amount, void (MacroAssembler::*emit_shift)(Register, Register)) {
1924  // Temporary registers cannot overlap with {dst}.
1925  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
1926 
1927  constexpr size_t kMaxRegMoves = 3;
1928  base::SmallVector<LiftoffAssembler::ParallelRegisterMoveTuple, kMaxRegMoves>
1929  reg_moves;
1930 
1931  // If {dst} contains {ecx}, replace it by an unused register, which is then
1932  // moved to {ecx} in the end.
1933  Register ecx_replace = no_reg;
1934  if (PairContains(dst, ecx)) {
1935  ecx_replace = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1936  dst = ReplaceInPair(dst, ecx, ecx_replace);
1937  // If {amount} needs to be moved to {ecx}, but {ecx} is in use (and not part
1938  // of {dst}, hence overwritten anyway), move {ecx} to a tmp register and
1939  // restore it at the end.
1940  } else if (amount != ecx &&
1941  (assm->cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(ecx)) ||
1942  pinned.has(LiftoffRegister(ecx)))) {
1943  ecx_replace = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1944  reg_moves.emplace_back(ecx_replace, ecx, kI32);
1945  }
1946 
1947  reg_moves.emplace_back(dst, src, kI64);
1948  reg_moves.emplace_back(ecx, amount, kI32);
1949  assm->ParallelRegisterMove(base::VectorOf(reg_moves));
1950 
1951  // Do the actual shift.
1952  (assm->*emit_shift)(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp());
1953 
1954  // Restore {ecx} if needed.
1955  if (ecx_replace != no_reg) assm->mov(ecx, ecx_replace);
1956 }
1957 } // namespace liftoff

1965 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shli(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
1966  int32_t amount) {
1967  amount &= 63;
1968  if (amount >= 32) {
1969  if (dst.high_gp() != src.low_gp()) mov(dst.high_gp(), src.low_gp());
1970  if (amount != 32) shl(dst.high_gp(), amount - 32);
1971  xor_(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp());
1972  } else {
1973  if (dst != src) Move(dst, src, kI64);
1974  ShlPair(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), amount);
1975  }
1976 }

2016 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_clz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2017  // return high == 0 ? 32 + CLZ32(low) : CLZ32(high);
2018  Label done;
2019  Register safe_dst = dst.low_gp();
2020  if (src.low_gp() == safe_dst) safe_dst = dst.high_gp();
2021  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LZCNT)) {
2022  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LZCNT);
2023  lzcnt(safe_dst, src.high_gp()); // Sets CF if high == 0.
2024  j(not_carry, &done, Label::kNear);
2025  lzcnt(safe_dst, src.low_gp());
2026  add(safe_dst, Immediate(32)); // 32 + CLZ32(low)
2027  } else {
2028  // CLZ32(x) =^ x == 0 ? 32 : 31 - BSR32(x)
2029  Label high_is_zero;
2030  bsr(safe_dst, src.high_gp()); // Sets ZF is high == 0.
2031  j(zero, &high_is_zero, Label::kNear);
2032  xor_(safe_dst, Immediate(31)); // for x in [0..31], 31^x == 31-x.
2033  jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
2034 
2035  bind(&high_is_zero);
2036  Label low_not_zero;
2037  bsr(safe_dst, src.low_gp());
2038  j(not_zero, &low_not_zero, Label::kNear);
2039  mov(safe_dst, Immediate(64 ^ 63)); // 64, after the xor below.
2040  bind(&low_not_zero);
2041  xor_(safe_dst, 63); // for x in [0..31], 63^x == 63-x.
2042  }
2043 
2044  bind(&done);
2045  if (safe_dst != dst.low_gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), safe_dst);
2046  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp()); // High word of result is always 0.
2047 }
2048 
2049 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_ctz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2050  // return low == 0 ? 32 + CTZ32(high) : CTZ32(low);
2051  Label done;
2052  Register safe_dst = dst.low_gp();
2053  if (src.high_gp() == safe_dst) safe_dst = dst.high_gp();
2054  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(BMI1)) {
2055  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, BMI1);
2056  tzcnt(safe_dst, src.low_gp()); // Sets CF if low == 0.
2057  j(not_carry, &done, Label::kNear);
2058  tzcnt(safe_dst, src.high_gp());
2059  add(safe_dst, Immediate(32)); // 32 + CTZ32(high)
2060  } else {
2061  // CTZ32(x) =^ x == 0 ? 32 : BSF32(x)
2062  bsf(safe_dst, src.low_gp()); // Sets ZF is low == 0.
2063  j(not_zero, &done, Label::kNear);
2064 
2065  Label high_not_zero;
2066  bsf(safe_dst, src.high_gp());
2067  j(not_zero, &high_not_zero, Label::kNear);
2068  mov(safe_dst, 64); // low == 0 and high == 0
2069  jmp(&done);
2070  bind(&high_not_zero);
2071  add(safe_dst, Immediate(32)); // 32 + CTZ32(high)
2072  }
2073 
2074  bind(&done);
2075  if (safe_dst != dst.low_gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), safe_dst);
2076  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp()); // High word of result is always 0.
2077 }
2078 
2079 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_popcnt(LiftoffRegister dst,
2080  LiftoffRegister src) {
2081  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(POPCNT)) return false;
2082  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, POPCNT);
2083  // Produce partial popcnts in the two dst registers.
2084  Register src1 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.high_gp() : src.low_gp();
2085  Register src2 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.low_gp() : src.high_gp();
2086  popcnt(dst.low_gp(), src1);
2087  popcnt(dst.high_gp(), src2);
2088  // Add the two into the lower dst reg, clear the higher dst reg.
2089  add(dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2090  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2091  return true;
2092 }

2154 namespace liftoff {
2155 enum class MinOrMax : uint8_t { kMin, kMax };
2156 template <typename type>
2157 inline void EmitFloatMinOrMax(LiftoffAssembler* assm, DoubleRegister dst,
2158  DoubleRegister lhs, DoubleRegister rhs,
2159  MinOrMax min_or_max) {
2160  Label is_nan;
2161  Label lhs_below_rhs;
2162  Label lhs_above_rhs;
2163  Label done;
2164 
2165  // We need one tmp register to extract the sign bit. Get it right at the
2166  // beginning, such that the spilling code is not accidentially jumped over.
2167  Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
2168 
2169 #define dop(name, ...) \
2170  do { \
2171  if (sizeof(type) == 4) { \
2172  assm->name##s(__VA_ARGS__); \
2173  } else { \
2174  assm->name##d(__VA_ARGS__); \
2175  } \
2176  } while (false)
2177 
2178  // Check the easy cases first: nan (e.g. unordered), smaller and greater.
2179  // NaN has to be checked first, because PF=1 implies CF=1.
2180  dop(ucomis, lhs, rhs);
2181  assm->j(parity_even, &is_nan, Label::kNear); // PF=1
2182  assm->j(below, &lhs_below_rhs, Label::kNear); // CF=1
2183  assm->j(above, &lhs_above_rhs, Label::kNear); // CF=0 && ZF=0
2184 
2185  // If we get here, then either
2186  // a) {lhs == rhs},
2187  // b) {lhs == -0.0} and {rhs == 0.0}, or
2188  // c) {lhs == 0.0} and {rhs == -0.0}.
2189  // For a), it does not matter whether we return {lhs} or {rhs}. Check the sign
2190  // bit of {rhs} to differentiate b) and c).
2191  dop(movmskp, tmp, rhs);
2192  assm->test(tmp, Immediate(1));
2193  assm->j(zero, &lhs_below_rhs, Label::kNear);
2194  assm->jmp(&lhs_above_rhs, Label::kNear);
2195 
2196  assm->bind(&is_nan);
2197  // Create a NaN output.
2198  dop(xorp, dst, dst);
2199  dop(divs, dst, dst);
2200  assm->jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
2201 
2202  assm->bind(&lhs_below_rhs);
2203  DoubleRegister lhs_below_rhs_src = min_or_max == MinOrMax::kMin ? lhs : rhs;
2204  if (dst != lhs_below_rhs_src) dop(movs, dst, lhs_below_rhs_src);
2205  assm->jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
2206 
2207  assm->bind(&lhs_above_rhs);
2208  DoubleRegister lhs_above_rhs_src = min_or_max == MinOrMax::kMin ? rhs : lhs;
2209  if (dst != lhs_above_rhs_src) dop(movs, dst, lhs_above_rhs_src);
2210 
2211  assm->bind(&done);
2212 }
2213 } // namespace liftoff
2214 
2215 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_min(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2216  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2217  liftoff::EmitFloatMinOrMax<float>(this, dst, lhs, rhs,
2218  liftoff::MinOrMax::kMin);
2219 }

2221 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_max(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2222  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2223  liftoff::EmitFloatMinOrMax<float>(this, dst, lhs, rhs,
2224  liftoff::MinOrMax::kMax);
2225 }
2226 
2227 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2228  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2229  static constexpr int kF32SignBit = 1 << 31;
2230  LiftoffRegList pinned;
2231  Register scratch = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
2232  Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2233  Movd(scratch, lhs); // move {lhs} into {scratch}.
2234  and_(scratch, Immediate(~kF32SignBit)); // clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2235  Movd(scratch2, rhs); // move {rhs} into {scratch2}.
2236  and_(scratch2, Immediate(kF32SignBit)); // isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2237  or_(scratch, scratch2); // combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2238  Movd(dst, scratch); // move result into {dst}.
2239 }

2354 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2355  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2356  static constexpr int kF32SignBit = 1 << 31;
2357  // On ia32, we cannot hold the whole f64 value in a gp register, so we just
2358  // operate on the upper half (UH).
2359  LiftoffRegList pinned;
2360  Register scratch = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
2361  Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2362 
2363  Pextrd(scratch, lhs, 1); // move UH of {lhs} into {scratch}.
2364  and_(scratch, Immediate(~kF32SignBit)); // clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2365  Pextrd(scratch2, rhs, 1); // move UH of {rhs} into {scratch2}.
2366  and_(scratch2, Immediate(kF32SignBit)); // isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2367  or_(scratch, scratch2); // combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2368  movsd(dst, lhs); // move {lhs} into {dst}.
2369  Pinsrd(dst, scratch, 1); // insert {scratch} into UH of {dst}.
2370 }

2430 #define __ assm->
2431 // Used for float to int conversions. If the value in {converted_back} equals
2432 // {src} afterwards, the conversion succeeded.
2433 template <typename dst_type, typename src_type>
2434 inline void ConvertFloatToIntAndBack(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
2435  DoubleRegister src,
2436  DoubleRegister converted_back,
2437  LiftoffRegList pinned) {
2438  if (std::is_same_v<double, src_type>) { // f64
2439  if (std::is_signed_v<dst_type>) { // f64 -> i32
2440  __ cvttsd2si(dst, src);
2441  __ Cvtsi2sd(converted_back, dst);
2442  } else { // f64 -> u32
2443  // Use converted_back as a scratch register (we can use it as it is an
2444  // "output" register of this function.
2445  __ Cvttsd2ui(dst, src, converted_back);
2446  __ Cvtui2sd(converted_back, dst,
2447  CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters(assm, pinned).Acquire());
2448  }
2449  } else { // f32
2450  if (std::is_signed_v<dst_type>) { // f32 -> i32
2451  __ cvttss2si(dst, src);
2452  __ Cvtsi2ss(converted_back, dst);
2453  } else { // f32 -> u32
2454  // Use converted_back as a scratch register (we can use it as it is an
2455  // "output" register of this function.
2456  __ Cvttss2ui(dst, src, converted_back);
2457  __ Cvtui2ss(converted_back, dst,
2458  CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters(assm, pinned).Acquire());
2459  }
2460  }
2461 }
2462 
2463 template <typename dst_type, typename src_type>
2464 inline void EmitTruncateFloatToInt(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
2465  DoubleRegister src, Label* trap) {
2466  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1)) {
2467  __ bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "no SSE4.1");
2468  return;
2469  }
2470  CpuFeatureScope feature(assm, SSE4_1);
2471 
2472  LiftoffRegList pinned{src, dst};
2473  // Note: This relies on ConvertFloatToIntAndBack not reusing these scratch
2474  // registers!
2475  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
2476  DoubleRegister converted_back = kScratchDoubleReg2;
2477 
2478  if (std::is_same_v<double, src_type>) { // f64
2479  __ roundsd(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2480  } else { // f32
2481  __ roundss(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2482  }
2483  ConvertFloatToIntAndBack<dst_type, src_type>(assm, dst, rounded,
2484  converted_back, pinned);
2485  if (std::is_same_v<double, src_type>) { // f64
2486  __ ucomisd(converted_back, rounded);
2487  } else { // f32
2488  __ ucomiss(converted_back, rounded);
2489  }
2490 
2491  // Jump to trap if PF is 0 (one of the operands was NaN) or they are not
2492  // equal.
2493  __ j(parity_even, trap);
2494  __ j(not_equal, trap);
2495 }
2496 
2497 template <typename dst_type, typename src_type>
2498 inline void EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
2499  DoubleRegister src) {
2500  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1)) {
2501  __ bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "no SSE4.1");
2502  return;
2503  }
2504  CpuFeatureScope feature(assm, SSE4_1);
2505 
2506  Label done;
2507  Label not_nan;
2508  Label src_positive;
2509 
2510  LiftoffRegList pinned{src, dst};
2511  DoubleRegister rounded =
2512  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2513  DoubleRegister converted_back =
2514  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2515  DoubleRegister zero_reg =
2516  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2517 
2518  if (std::is_same_v<double, src_type>) { // f64
2519  __ roundsd(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2520  } else { // f32
2521  __ roundss(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2522  }
2523 
2524  ConvertFloatToIntAndBack<dst_type, src_type>(assm, dst, rounded,
2525  converted_back, pinned);
2526  if (std::is_same_v<double, src_type>) { // f64
2527  __ ucomisd(converted_back, rounded);
2528  } else { // f32
2529  __ ucomiss(converted_back, rounded);
2530  }
2531 
2532  // Return 0 if PF is 0 (one of the operands was NaN)
2533  __ j(parity_odd, &not_nan);
2534  __ xor_(dst, dst);
2535  __ jmp(&done);
2536 
2537  __ bind(&not_nan);
2538  // If rounding is as expected, return result
2539  __ j(equal, &done);
2540 
2541  __ Xorpd(zero_reg, zero_reg);
2542 
2543  // if out-of-bounds, check if src is positive
2544  if (std::is_same_v<double, src_type>) { // f64
2545  __ ucomisd(src, zero_reg);
2546  } else { // f32
2547  __ ucomiss(src, zero_reg);
2548  }
2549  __ j(above, &src_positive);
2550  __ mov(dst, Immediate(std::numeric_limits<dst_type>::min()));
2551  __ jmp(&done);
2552 
2553  __ bind(&src_positive);
2554 
2555  __ mov(dst, Immediate(std::numeric_limits<dst_type>::max()));
2556 
2557  __ bind(&done);
2558 }
2559 #undef __
2560 } // namespace liftoff

2562 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
2563  LiftoffRegister dst,
2564  LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
2565  switch (opcode) {
2566  case kExprI32ConvertI64:
2567  if (dst.gp() != src.low_gp()) mov(dst.gp(), src.low_gp());
2568  return true;
2569  case kExprI32SConvertF32:
2570  liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(), src.fp(),
2571  trap);
2572  return true;
2573  case kExprI32UConvertF32:
2574  liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(), src.fp(),
2575  trap);
2576  return true;
2577  case kExprI32SConvertF64:
2578  liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(), src.fp(),
2579  trap);
2580  return true;
2581  case kExprI32UConvertF64:
2582  liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(),
2583  src.fp(), trap);
2584  return true;
2585  case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
2586  liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(),
2587  src.fp());
2588  return true;
2589  case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
2590  liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(),
2591  src.fp());
2592  return true;
2593  case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
2594  liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(),
2595  src.fp());
2596  return true;
2597  case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
2598  liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(),
2599  src.fp());
2600  return true;
2601  case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
2602  Movd(dst.gp(), src.fp());
2603  return true;
2604  case kExprI64SConvertI32:
2605  if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2606  if (dst.high_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.high_gp(), src.gp());
2607  sar(dst.high_gp(), 31);
2608  return true;
2609  case kExprI64UConvertI32:
2610  if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2611  xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2612  return true;
2613  case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
2614  // Push src to the stack.
2615  AllocateStackSpace(8);
2616  movsd(Operand(esp, 0), src.fp());
2617  // Pop to dst.
2618  pop(dst.low_gp());
2619  pop(dst.high_gp());
2620  return true;
2621  case kExprF32SConvertI32:
2622  cvtsi2ss(dst.fp(), src.gp());
2623  return true;
2624  case kExprF32UConvertI32: {
2625  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src};
2626  Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2627  Cvtui2ss(dst.fp(), src.gp(), scratch);
2628  return true;
2629  }
2630  case kExprF32ConvertF64:
2631  cvtsd2ss(dst.fp(), src.fp());
2632  return true;
2633  case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
2634  Movd(dst.fp(), src.gp());
2635  return true;
2636  case kExprF64SConvertI32:
2637  Cvtsi2sd(dst.fp(), src.gp());
2638  return true;
2639  case kExprF64UConvertI32: {
2640  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src};
2641  Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2642  Cvtui2sd(dst.fp(), src.gp(), scratch);
2643  return true;
2644  }
2645  case kExprF64ConvertF32:
2646  cvtss2sd(dst.fp(), src.fp());
2647  return true;
2648  case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
2649  // Push src to the stack.
2650  push(src.high_gp());
2651  push(src.low_gp());
2652  // Pop to dst.
2653  movsd(dst.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
2654  add(esp, Immediate(8));
2655  return true;
2656  default:
2657  return false;
2658  }
2659 }

2695 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
2696  ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
2697  Register rhs,
2698  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2699  if (rhs != no_reg) {
2700  switch (kind) {
2701  case kRef:
2702  case kRefNull:
2703  DCHECK(cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual);
2704  [[fallthrough]];
2705  case kI32:
2706  cmp(lhs, rhs);
2707  break;
2708  default:
2709  UNREACHABLE();
2710  }
2711  } else {
2712  DCHECK_EQ(kind, kI32);
2713  test(lhs, lhs);
2714  }
2715 
2716  j(cond, label);
2717 }

2755 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_eqz(Register dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2756  // Compute the OR of both registers in the src pair, using dst as scratch
2757  // register. Then check whether the result is equal to zero.
2758  if (src.low_gp() == dst) {
2759  or_(dst, src.high_gp());
2760  } else {
2761  if (src.high_gp() != dst) mov(dst, src.high_gp());
2762  or_(dst, src.low_gp());
2763  }
2764  liftoff::setcc_32(this, equal, dst);
2765 }

2768 inline Condition cond_make_unsigned(Condition cond) {
2769  switch (cond) {
2770  case kLessThan:
2771  return kUnsignedLessThan;
2772  case kLessThanEqual:
2773  return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
2774  case kGreaterThan:
2775  return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
2776  case kGreaterThanEqual:
2777  return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
2778  default:
2779  return cond;
2780  }
2781 }

2784 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2785  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2786  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2787  Condition unsigned_cond = liftoff::cond_make_unsigned(cond);
2788 
2789  // Get the tmp byte register out here, such that we don't conditionally spill
2790  // (this cannot be reflected in the cache state).
2791  Register tmp_byte_reg = liftoff::GetTmpByteRegister(this, dst);
2792 
2793  // For signed i64 comparisons, we still need to use unsigned comparison for
2794  // the low word (the only bit carrying signedness information is the MSB in
2795  // the high word).
2796  Label setcc;
2797  Label cont;
2798  // Compare high word first. If it differs, use if for the setcc. If it's
2799  // equal, compare the low word and use that for setcc.
2800  cmp(lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
2801  j(not_equal, &setcc, Label::kNear);
2802  cmp(lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2803  if (unsigned_cond != cond) {
2804  // If the condition predicate for the low differs from that for the high
2805  // word, emit a separete setcc sequence for the low word.
2806  liftoff::setcc_32_no_spill(this, unsigned_cond, dst, tmp_byte_reg);
2807  jmp(&cont);
2808  }
2809  bind(&setcc);
2810  liftoff::setcc_32_no_spill(this, cond, dst, tmp_byte_reg);
2811  bind(&cont);
2812 }
2813 
2814 namespace liftoff {
2815 template <void (Assembler::*cmp_op)(DoubleRegister, DoubleRegister)>
2816 void EmitFloatSetCond(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Condition cond, Register dst,
2817  DoubleRegister lhs, DoubleRegister rhs) {
2818  Label cont;
2819  Label not_nan;
2820 
2821  // Get the tmp byte register out here, such that we don't conditionally spill
2822  // (this cannot be reflected in the cache state).
2823  Register tmp_byte_reg = GetTmpByteRegister(assm, dst);
2824 
2825  (assm->*cmp_op)(lhs, rhs);
2826  // If PF is one, one of the operands was Nan. This needs special handling.
2827  assm->j(parity_odd, &not_nan, Label::kNear);
2828  // Return 1 for f32.ne, 0 for all other cases.
2829  if (cond == not_equal) {
2830  assm->mov(dst, Immediate(1));
2831  } else {
2832  assm->xor_(dst, dst);
2833  }
2834  assm->jmp(&cont, Label::kNear);
2835  assm->bind(&not_nan);
2836 
2837  setcc_32_no_spill(assm, cond, dst, tmp_byte_reg);
2838  assm->bind(&cont);
2839 }

2870 template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, XMMRegister),
2871  void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister)>
2872 void EmitSimdCommutativeBinOp(
2873  LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2874  LiftoffRegister rhs, std::optional<CpuFeature> feature = std::nullopt) {
2875  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2876  CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2877  (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp());
2878  return;
2879  }
2880 
2881  std::optional<CpuFeatureScope> sse_scope;
2882  if (feature.has_value()) sse_scope.emplace(assm, *feature);
2883 
2884  if (dst.fp() == rhs.fp()) {
2885  (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2886  } else {
2887  if (dst.fp() != lhs.fp()) (assm->movaps)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2888  (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), rhs.fp());
2889  }
2890 }

2892 template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, XMMRegister),
2893  void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister)>
2894 void EmitSimdNonCommutativeBinOp(
2895  LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2896  LiftoffRegister rhs, std::optional<CpuFeature> feature = std::nullopt) {
2897  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2898  CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2899  (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp());
2900  return;
2901  }
2902 
2903  std::optional<CpuFeatureScope> sse_scope;
2904  if (feature.has_value()) sse_scope.emplace(assm, *feature);
2905 
2906  if (dst.fp() == rhs.fp()) {
2907  assm->movaps(kScratchDoubleReg, rhs.fp());
2908  assm->movaps(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2909  (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
2910  } else {
2911  if (dst.fp() != lhs.fp()) assm->movaps(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2912  (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), rhs.fp());
2913  }
2914 }

2916 template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, XMMRegister),
2917  void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister), uint8_t width>
2918 void EmitSimdShiftOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2919  LiftoffRegister operand, LiftoffRegister count) {
2920  static constexpr RegClass tmp_rc = reg_class_for(kI32);
2921  LiftoffRegister tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(tmp_rc, LiftoffRegList{count});
2922  constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1;
2923 
2924  assm->mov(tmp.gp(), count.gp());
2925  assm->and_(tmp.gp(), Immediate(mask));
2926  assm->Movd(kScratchDoubleReg, tmp.gp());
2927  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2928  CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2929  (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), operand.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
2930  } else {
2931  if (dst.fp() != operand.fp()) assm->movaps(dst.fp(), operand.fp());
2932  (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
2933  }
2934 }
2935 
2936 template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, uint8_t),
2937  void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, uint8_t), uint8_t width>
2938 void EmitSimdShiftOpImm(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2939  LiftoffRegister operand, int32_t count) {
2940  constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1;
2941  uint8_t shift = static_cast<uint8_t>(count & mask);
2942  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2943  CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2944  (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), operand.fp(), shift);
2945  } else {
2946  if (dst.fp() != operand.fp()) assm->movaps(dst.fp(), operand.fp());
2947  (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), shift);
2948  }
2949 }

2951 inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2952  LiftoffRegister src) {
2953  Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst}).gp();
2954  assm->xor_(tmp, tmp);
2955  assm->mov(dst.gp(), Immediate(1));
2956  assm->Ptest(src.fp(), src.fp());
2957  assm->cmov(zero, dst.gp(), tmp);
2958 }
2959 
2960 template <void (SharedMacroAssemblerBase::*pcmp)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister)>
2961 inline void EmitAllTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2962  LiftoffRegister src,
2963  std::optional<CpuFeature> feature = std::nullopt) {
2964  std::optional<CpuFeatureScope> sse_scope;
2965  if (feature.has_value()) sse_scope.emplace(assm, *feature);
2966 
2967  Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst}).gp();
2968  XMMRegister tmp_simd = liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg;
2969  assm->mov(tmp, Immediate(1));
2970  assm->xor_(dst.gp(), dst.gp());
2971  assm->Pxor(tmp_simd, tmp_simd);
2972  (assm->*pcmp)(tmp_simd, src.fp());
2973  assm->Ptest(tmp_simd, tmp_simd);
2974  assm->cmov(zero, dst.gp(), tmp);
2975 }
