2979 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2980  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2981  LoadType type,
2982  LoadTransformationKind transform,
2983  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2984  bool i64_offset) {
2985  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
2986  Operand src_op{src_addr, offset_reg, times_1,
2987  static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm)};
2988  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2989 
2990  MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2991  if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2992  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2993  Pmovsxbw(dst.fp(), src_op);
2994  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2995  Pmovzxbw(dst.fp(), src_op);
2996  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2997  Pmovsxwd(dst.fp(), src_op);
2998  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2999  Pmovzxwd(dst.fp(), src_op);
3000  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3001  Pmovsxdq(dst.fp(), src_op);
3002  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
3003  Pmovzxdq(dst.fp(), src_op);
3004  }
3005  } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
3006  if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3007  Movss(dst.fp(), src_op);
3008  } else {
3009  DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
3010  Movsd(dst.fp(), src_op);
3011  }
3012  } else {
3013  DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
3014  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
3015  S128Load8Splat(dst.fp(), src_op, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3016  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
3017  S128Load16Splat(dst.fp(), src_op, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3018  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3019  S128Load32Splat(dst.fp(), src_op);
3020  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
3021  Movddup(dst.fp(), src_op);
3022  }
3023  }
3024 }

3026 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
3027  Register addr, Register offset_reg,
3028  uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
3029  uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
3030  bool /* i64_offset */) {
3031  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
3032  Operand src_op{addr, offset_reg, times_1, static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm)};
3033  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
3034 
3035  MachineType mem_type = type.mem_type();
3036  if (mem_type == MachineType::Int8()) {
3037  Pinsrb(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op, laneidx);
3038  } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int16()) {
3039  Pinsrw(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op, laneidx);
3040  } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int32()) {
3041  Pinsrd(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op, laneidx);
3042  } else {
3043  DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), mem_type);
3044  if (laneidx == 0) {
3045  Movlps(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op);
3046  } else {
3047  DCHECK_EQ(1, laneidx);
3048  Movhps(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op);
3049  }
3050  }
3051 }

3053 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,
3054  uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
3055  StoreType type, uint8_t lane,
3056  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
3057  bool /* i64_offset */) {
3058  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
3059  Operand dst_op = Operand(dst, offset, times_1, offset_imm);
3060  if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
3061 
3062  MachineRepresentation rep = type.mem_rep();
3063  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
3064  Pextrb(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3065  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
3066  Pextrw(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3067  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
3068  S128Store32Lane(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3069  } else {
3070  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kWord64, rep);
3071  S128Store64Lane(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3072  }
3073 }

3075 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
3076  LiftoffRegister lhs,
3077  LiftoffRegister rhs,
3078  const uint8_t shuffle[16],
3079  bool is_swizzle) {
3080  LiftoffRegister tmp = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
3081  // Prepare 16 byte aligned buffer for shuffle control mask.
3082  mov(tmp.gp(), esp);
3083  and_(esp, -16);
3084 
3085  if (is_swizzle) {
3086  uint32_t imms[4];
3087  // Shuffles that use just 1 operand are called swizzles, rhs can be ignored.
3088  wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack16Lanes(imms, shuffle);
3089  for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3090  push_imm32(imms[i]);
3091  }
3092  Pshufb(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
3093  mov(esp, tmp.gp());
3094  return;
3095  }
3096 
3097  movups(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, lhs.fp());
3098  for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3099  uint32_t mask = 0;
3100  for (int j = 3; j >= 0; j--) {
3101  uint8_t lane = shuffle[i * 4 + j];
3102  mask <<= 8;
3103  mask |= lane < kSimd128Size ? lane : 0x80;
3104  }
3105  push(Immediate(mask));
3106  }
3107  Pshufb(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, lhs.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
3108 
3109  for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3110  uint32_t mask = 0;
3111  for (int j = 3; j >= 0; j--) {
3112  uint8_t lane = shuffle[i * 4 + j];
3113  mask <<= 8;
3114  mask |= lane >= kSimd128Size ? (lane & 0x0F) : 0x80;
3115  }
3116  push(Immediate(mask));
3117  }
3118  Pshufb(dst.fp(), rhs.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
3119  Por(dst.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3120  mov(esp, tmp.gp());
3121 }

3409 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_gt_s(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3410  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3411  // Different register alias requirements depending on CpuFeatures supported:
3412  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) || CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_2)) {
3413  // 1. AVX, or SSE4_2 no requirements (I64x2GtS takes care of aliasing).
3414  I64x2GtS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3415  } else {
3416  // 2. Else, dst != lhs && dst != rhs (lhs == rhs is ok).
3417  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3418  LiftoffRegister tmp =
3419  GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs});
3420  I64x2GtS(tmp.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3421  movaps(dst.fp(), tmp.fp());
3422  } else {
3423  I64x2GtS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3424  }
3425  }
3426 }
3427 
3428 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_ge_s(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3429  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3430  // Different register alias requirements depending on CpuFeatures supported:
3431  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
3432  // 1. AVX, no requirements.
3433  I64x2GeS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3434  } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_2)) {
3435  // 2. SSE4_2, dst != lhs.
3436  if (dst == lhs) {
3437  LiftoffRegister tmp =
3438  GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kFpReg, {rhs}, LiftoffRegList{lhs});
3439  // macro-assembler uses kScratchDoubleReg, so don't use it.
3440  I64x2GeS(tmp.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3441  movaps(dst.fp(), tmp.fp());
3442  } else {
3443  I64x2GeS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3444  }
3445  } else {
3446  // 3. Else, dst != lhs && dst != rhs (lhs == rhs is ok).
3447  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3448  LiftoffRegister tmp =
3449  GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs});
3450  I64x2GeS(tmp.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3451  movaps(dst.fp(), tmp.fp());
3452  } else {
3453  I64x2GeS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3454  }
3455  }
3456 }

3510 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_const(LiftoffRegister dst,
3511  const uint8_t imms[16]) {
3512  uint64_t vals[2];
3513  memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
3514  MacroAssembler::Move(dst.fp(), vals[0]);
3515 
3516  uint64_t high = vals[1];
3517  Register tmp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {}).gp();
3518  MacroAssembler::Move(tmp, Immediate(high & 0xffff'ffff));
3519  Pinsrd(dst.fp(), tmp, 2);
3520 
3521  MacroAssembler::Move(tmp, Immediate(high >> 32));
3522  Pinsrd(dst.fp(), tmp, 3);
3523 }

3547 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_select(LiftoffRegister dst,
3548  LiftoffRegister src1,
3549  LiftoffRegister src2,
3550  LiftoffRegister mask) {
3551  // Ensure that we don't overwrite any inputs with the movaps below.
3552  DCHECK_NE(dst, src1);
3553  DCHECK_NE(dst, src2);
3554  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && dst != mask) {
3555  movaps(dst.fp(), mask.fp());
3556  S128Select(dst.fp(), dst.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.fp(),
3557  liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3558  } else {
3559  S128Select(dst.fp(), mask.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.fp(),
3560  liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3561  }
3562 }

3921  } else {

3924  }

4039 namespace liftoff {
4040 // Helper function to check for register aliasing, AVX support, and moves
4041 // registers around before calling the actual macro-assembler function.
4042 inline void I32x4ExtMulHelper(LiftoffAssembler* assm, XMMRegister dst,
4043  XMMRegister src1, XMMRegister src2, bool low,
4044  bool is_signed) {
4045  // I32x4ExtMul requires dst == src1 if AVX is not supported.
4046  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) || dst == src1) {
4047  assm->I32x4ExtMul(dst, src1, src2, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, low,
4048  is_signed);
4049  } else if (dst != src2) {
4050  // dst != src1 && dst != src2
4051  assm->movaps(dst, src1);
4052  assm->I32x4ExtMul(dst, dst, src2, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, low,
4053  is_signed);
4054  } else {
4055  // dst == src2
4056  // Extended multiplication is commutative,
4057  assm->movaps(dst, src2);
4058  assm->I32x4ExtMul(dst, dst, src1, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, low,
4059  is_signed);
4060  }
4061 }
4062 } // namespace liftoff
4063 
4064 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_extmul_low_i16x8_s(LiftoffRegister dst,
4065  LiftoffRegister src1,
4066  LiftoffRegister src2) {
4067  liftoff::I32x4ExtMulHelper(this, dst.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.fp(), /*low=*/true,
4068  /*is_signed=*/true);
4069 }

4466 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_sconvert_i32x4(LiftoffRegister dst,
4467  LiftoffRegister src) {
4468  Cvtdq2ps(dst.fp(), src.fp());
4469 }
4470 
4471 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_uconvert_i32x4(LiftoffRegister dst,
4472  LiftoffRegister src) {
4473  Pxor(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Zeros.
4474  Pblendw(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp(),
4475  uint8_t{0x55}); // Get lo 16 bits.
4476  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
4477  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, AVX);
4478  vpsubd(dst.fp(), src.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Get hi 16 bits.
4479  } else {
4480  if (dst.fp() != src.fp()) movaps(dst.fp(), src.fp());
4481  psubd(dst.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
4482  }
4483  Cvtdq2ps(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg,
4484  liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Convert lo exactly.
4485  Psrld(dst.fp(), dst.fp(), uint8_t{1}); // Div by 2 to get in unsigned range.
4486  Cvtdq2ps(dst.fp(), dst.fp()); // Convert hi, exactly.
4487  Addps(dst.fp(), dst.fp(), dst.fp()); // Double hi, exactly.
4488  Addps(dst.fp(), dst.fp(),
4489  liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Add hi and lo, may round.
4490 }
4491

4494  Cvtpd2ps(dst.fp(), src.fp());
4495 }

4674 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_replace_lane(LiftoffRegister dst,
4675  LiftoffRegister src1,
4676  LiftoffRegister src2,
4677  uint8_t imm_lane_idx) {
4678  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
4679  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, AVX);
4680  vpinsrb(dst.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.gp(), imm_lane_idx);
4681  } else {
4682  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SSE4_1);
4683  if (dst.fp() != src1.fp()) movaps(dst.fp(), src1.fp());
4684  pinsrb(dst.fp(), src2.gp(), imm_lane_idx);
4685  }
4686 }

4692  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
4693  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, AVX);
4694  vpinsrw(dst.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.gp(), imm_lane_idx);
4695  } else {
4696  if (dst.fp() != src1.fp()) movaps(dst.fp(), src1.fp());
4697  pinsrw(dst.fp(), src2.gp(), imm_lane_idx);
4698  }
4699 }

4701 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_replace_lane(LiftoffRegister dst,
4702  LiftoffRegister src1,
4703  LiftoffRegister src2,
4704  uint8_t imm_lane_idx) {
4705  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
4706  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, AVX);
4707  vpinsrd(dst.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.gp(), imm_lane_idx);
4708  } else {
4709  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SSE4_1);

4715 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_replace_lane(LiftoffRegister dst,

4731 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_replace_lane(LiftoffRegister dst,

4965 void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
4966  LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
4967  while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
4968  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4969  push(reg.gp());
4970  gp_regs.clear(reg);
4971  }
4972  LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
4973  unsigned num_fp_regs = fp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
4974  if (num_fp_regs) {
4975  AllocateStackSpace(num_fp_regs * kSimd128Size);
4976  unsigned offset = 0;
4977  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4978  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4979  Movdqu(Operand(esp, offset), reg.fp());
4980  fp_regs.clear(reg);
4981  offset += kSimd128Size;
4982  }
4983  DCHECK_EQ(offset, num_fp_regs * kSimd128Size);
4984  }
4985 }
4986 
4987 void LiftoffAssembler::PopRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
4988  LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
4989  unsigned fp_offset = 0;
4990  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4991  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4992  Movdqu(reg.fp(), Operand(esp, fp_offset));
4993  fp_regs.clear(reg);
4994  fp_offset += kSimd128Size;
4995  }
4996  if (fp_offset) add(esp, Immediate(fp_offset));
4997  LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
4998  while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
4999  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
5000  pop(reg.gp());
5001  gp_regs.clear(reg);
5002  }
5003 }

5005 void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
5006  SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
5007  LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
5008  LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
5009  int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
5010  LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
5011  while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
5012  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetFirstRegSet();
5013  if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
5014  safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
5015  }
5016  gp_spills.clear(reg);
5017  ++spill_offset;
5018  spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
5019  }
5020  // Record the number of additional spill slots.
5021  RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
5022 }

5024 void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
5025  DCHECK_LT(num_stack_slots,
5026  (1 << 16) / kSystemPointerSize); // 16 bit immediate
5027  ret(static_cast<int>(num_stack_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
5028 }
5029 
5030 void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
5031  const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
5032  ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
5033  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
5034  AllocateStackSpace(stack_bytes);
5035 
5036  int arg_offset = 0;
5037  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
5038  if (arg.is_reg()) {
5039  liftoff::Store(this, esp, arg_offset, arg.reg(), arg.kind());
5040  } else if (arg.is_const()) {
5041  DCHECK_EQ(kI32, arg.kind());
5042  mov(Operand(esp, arg_offset), Immediate(arg.i32_const()));
5043  } else if (value_kind_size(arg.kind()) == 4) {
5044  // We do not have a scratch register, so move via the stack. Note that
5045  // {push} decrements {esp} by 4 and {pop} increments it again, but the
5046  // destionation operand uses the {esp} value after increasing.
5047  push(liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
5048  pop(Operand(esp, arg_offset));
5049  } else {
5050  DCHECK_EQ(8, value_kind_size(arg.kind()));
5051  push(liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
5052  pop(Operand(esp, arg_offset + 4));
5053  push(liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset() + 4));
5054  pop(Operand(esp, arg_offset));
5055  }
5056  arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
5057  }
5058  DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
5059 
5060  constexpr Register kScratch = eax;
5061  constexpr Register kArgumentBuffer = ecx;
5062  constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
5063  mov(kArgumentBuffer, esp);
5064  PrepareCallCFunction(kNumCCallArgs, kScratch);
5065 
5066  // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function. ia32
5067  // does not use registers here, so push to the stack.
5068  mov(Operand(esp, 0), kArgumentBuffer);
5069 
5070  // Now call the C function.
5071  CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
5072 
5073  // Move return value to the right register.
5074  const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
5075  if (return_kind != kVoid) {
5076  constexpr Register kReturnReg = eax;
5077  if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
5078  Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
5079  }
5080  ++next_result_reg;
5081  }
5082 
5083  // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
5084  if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
5085  liftoff::Load(this, *next_result_reg, esp, 0, out_argument_kind);
5086  }
5087 
5088  add(esp, Immediate(stack_bytes));
5089 }
5090 
5091 void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args,
5092  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
5093  LiftoffRegList arg_regs;
5094  for (const VarState arg : args) {
5095  if (arg.is_reg()) arg_regs.set(arg.reg());
5096  }
5097 
5098  RegList usable_regs = kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs - arg_regs.GetGpList();
5099  Register scratch = usable_regs.first();
5100  int num_lowered_args = 0;
5101  // i64 arguments are lowered to two actual arguments (taking two stack slots).
5102  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
5103  num_lowered_args += arg.kind() == kI64 ? 2 : 1;
5104  }
5105  PrepareCallCFunction(num_lowered_args, scratch);
5106 
5107  // Ia32 passes all arguments via the stack. Store them now in the stack space
5108  // allocated by {PrepareCallCFunction}.
5109 
5110  // GetNextOperand returns the operand for the next stack slot on each
5111  // invocation.
5112  auto GetNextOperand = [arg_offset = 0, num_lowered_args]() mutable {
5113  // Check that we don't exceed the pre-computed {num_stack_slots}.
5114  DCHECK_GE(num_lowered_args, arg_offset);
5115  USE(num_lowered_args);
5116  return Operand{esp, arg_offset++ * kSystemPointerSize};
5117  };
5118  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
5119  Operand dst = GetNextOperand();
5120  if (arg.is_reg()) {
5121  LiftoffRegister reg = arg.reg();
5122  if (arg.kind() == kI64) {
5123  mov(dst, reg.low_gp());
5124  mov(GetNextOperand(), reg.high_gp());
5125  } else {
5126  mov(dst, reg.gp());
5127  }
5128  } else if (arg.is_const()) {
5129  DCHECK_EQ(kI32, arg.kind());
5130  mov(dst, Immediate(arg.i32_const()));
5131  } else {
5132  DCHECK(arg.is_stack());
5133  if (arg.kind() == kI64) {
5134  mov(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
5135  mov(dst, scratch);
5136  mov(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset() + kSystemPointerSize));
5137  mov(GetNextOperand(), scratch);
5138  } else {
5139  mov(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
5140  mov(dst, scratch);
5141  }
5142  }
5143  }
5144 
5145  // Now call the C function.
5146  CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_lowered_args);
5147 }

5191 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
5192  DoubleRegister src,
5193  ValueKind kind) {

5195  ucomiss(src, src);

5197  DCHECK_EQ(kind, kF64);

5206 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
5207  LiftoffRegister src,
5208  Register tmp_gp,
5209  LiftoffRegister tmp_s128,
5210  ValueKind lane_kind) {
5211  if (lane_kind == kF32) {

5226 
5227 void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
5228  DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
5229  SortInPushOrder();
5230  int last_stack_slot = param_slots;
5231  for (auto& slot : slots_) {
5232  const int stack_slot = slot.dst_slot_;
5233  int stack_decrement = (last_stack_slot - stack_slot) * kSystemPointerSize;
5234  DCHECK_LT(0, stack_decrement);
5235  last_stack_slot = stack_slot;
5236  const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src = slot.src_;
5237  switch (src.loc()) {
5238  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack:
5239  // The combination of AllocateStackSpace and 2 movdqu is usually smaller
5240  // in code size than doing 4 pushes.
5241  if (src.kind() == kS128) {
5242  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement);
5243  asm_->movdqu(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg,
5244  liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
5245  asm_->movdqu(Operand(esp, 0), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
5246  break;
5247  }
5248  if (src.kind() == kF64) {
5249  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kDoubleSize);
5250  DCHECK_EQ(kLowWord, slot.half_);
5251  asm_->push(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(slot.src_offset_, kHighWord));
5252  stack_decrement = kSystemPointerSize;
5253  }
5254  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5255  asm_->push(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(slot.src_offset_, slot.half_));
5256  break;
5257  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister:
5258  if (src.kind() == kI64) {
5259  liftoff::push(
5260  asm_, slot.half_ == kLowWord ? src.reg().low() : src.reg().high(),
5261  kI32, stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5262  } else {
5263  int pushed_bytes = SlotSizeInBytes(slot);
5264  liftoff::push(asm_, src.reg(), src.kind(),
5265  stack_decrement - pushed_bytes);
5266  }
5267  break;
5268  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst:
5269  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5270  // The high word is the sign extension of the low word.
5271  asm_->push(Immediate(slot.half_ == kLowWord ? src.i32_const()
5272  : src.i32_const() >> 31));
5273  break;
5274  }
5275  }
5276 }
5277 
5278 #undef RETURN_FALSE_IF_MISSING_CPU_FEATURE
5279 
5280 } // namespace v8::internal::wasm
5281 
5282 #endif // V8_WASM_BASELINE_IA32_LIFTOFF_ASSEMBLER_IA32_INL_H_
